AtomLink(Uri, String)

Initializes a new instance of the AtomLink class using the supplied Uri and link relation type.

Declaration
public AtomLink(Uri href, string relation)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Uri href

A Uri that represents an IRI that identifies the location of this Web resource.
System.String relation

A value that indicates the link relation type.
Remarks

The Atom specification defines five initial values for the Registry of Link Relations:

  • alternate: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies an alternate version of the resource described by the containing element.
  • related: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource related to the resource described by the containing element.
  • self: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource equivalent to the containing element.
  • enclosure: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a related resource that is potentially large in size and might require special handling.
  • via: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource that is the source of the information provided in the containing element.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The href is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

Relation

Gets or sets a value that indicates the link relation type of this Web resource.

Declaration
public string Relation { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

A value that indicates the link relation type.
Remarks

If the Relation property is not specified, the AtomLink must be interpreted as if the link relation type is alternate.

The value of the Relation property must be a string that is non-empty and matches either the isegment-nz-nc or the IRI production in RFC 3987: Internationalized Resource Identifiers (IRIs). Note that use of a relative reference other than a simple name is not allowed. If a name is given, implementations must consider the link relation type equivalent to the same name registered within the IANA Registry of Link Relations (Section 7), and thus to the IRI that would be obtained by appending the value of the rel attribute to the string "http://www.iana.org/assignments/relation/". The value of Relation property describes the meaning of the link, but does not impose any behavioral requirements on Atom Processors.

The Atom specification defines five initial values for the Registry of Link Relations:

  • alternate: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies an alternate version of the resource described by the containing element.
  • related: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource related to the resource described by the containing element.
  • self: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource equivalent to the containing element.
  • enclosure: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a related resource that is potentially large in size and might require special handling.
  • via: Signifies that the IRI in the value of the Uri property identifies a resource that is the source of the information provided in the containing element.

FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension>)

Searches for a syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, and returns the first occurrence within the Extensions collection.

Declaration
public ISyndicationExtension FindExtension(Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.Predicate<ISyndicationExtension> match

The System.Predicate<T> delegate that defines the conditions of the ISyndicationExtension to search for.
Returns
Type Description
ISyndicationExtension

The first syndication extension that matches the conditions defined by the specified predicate, if found; otherwise, the default value for ISyndicationExtension.
Remarks

The System.Predicate<T> is a delegate to a method that returns true if the object passed to it matches the conditions defined in the delegate. The elements of the current Extensions are individually passed to the System.Predicate<T> delegate, moving forward in the Extensions, starting with the first element and ending with the last element. Processing is stopped when a match is found.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The match is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).
